item.title: Remove ^-^ fixed
item.dc:creator: @system system
item.description:
@system wrote:

[quote=“sk8rdude461, post:4, topic:508631”][quote author=Lil_Smok3r link=topic=626870.msg4261559#msg4261559 date=1363508031]
Can’t be on skype atm. My laptop’s charger ripped (don’t ask me about it -_-’) and laptop has no charge.

Follow these steps:

  1. www.canyouseeme.org
  2. Check the port you opened (43594/5555)
    2 1/2. If it shows an error. Portforward again. Advance onto 3 if Success.
  3. Go to client.java (Client sided)
  4. Check if you’ve changed ip.
  5. ^^^^^DONE^^^^^

If it’s a PI check your server.java too, Although you may not have it in there.
[/quote]
You missed a step.

  1. Run your server. (verify it’s fully started)
  2. Check your port on canyouseeme.org

Why make sure it’s running first?
canyouseeme only checks if the port is broadcasting (i.e, something is being sent from your IP out on the port).
So if the server (or what ever is supposed to be running on a given port) isn’t running. Nothing is being broadcast. So canyouseeme can’t tell if it’s on or not.[/quote]
I assumed he’d know that he will have the server running >.>

Read full topic
